Vol / Page:  15
Edition:
Quote:  (H.A.L. Laing) Jackie Howe: The familiar navy or black woollen singlet worn by Australian and New Zealand shearers and bushmen. It is named after Jackie Howe, an Australian shearer who in

1892 established a world shearing record by shearing 321 Merinoes with hand shears in 8hr 40 min.[check time see below ??]
